Class IdBasedGraphMem

Direct Known Subclasses:
SWClGraphMem
public class IdBasedGraphMem
extends com.hp.hpl.jena.graph.impl.GraphBase
implements IdBasedGraph

An RDF graph implemented using on six main memory-based indexes (S, P, O, SP, PO, SO). This implementation is optimized for read-only access. Removing triples from this graph is not supported.

Author:
Olaf Hartig

containedIds

protected final Set<Integer> containedIds
A set that holds the identifiers of all nodes that occur in the triples of this graph. This set allows to answer triple pattern queries (i.e. find queries) that contain unknown nodes (unknown to this graph) very fast because for this graph cannot contain triples that match the pattern.

graphBaseFind

protected com.hp.hpl.jena.util.iterator.ExtendedIterator<Triple> graphBaseFind(TripleMatch m)
The standard method that implements the execution of a triple pattern query. This method obtains the identifiers for the concrete components of the given triple pattern and facilitates the identifier-based find method (i.e. find(int, int, int)).
